            "notes": "This deck revolves around utilizing lands as a resource to establish a powerful engine with The Gitrog Monster as the commander. By utilizing cards that interact with lands such as Life from the Loam, Sylvan Safekeeper, and Exploration, the deck aims to generate value from sacrificing lands to draw cards and fuel its combo potential. With cards like Crop Rotation and Expedition Map to tutor for key lands like Cabal Coffers and Urborg, Tomb of Yawgmoth, the deck can generate large amounts of mana to cast powerful spells and creatures like Emrakul, the Promised End. The goal is to overwhelm the opponent with a powerful land-based engine while setting up for a game-ending combo or value play."
